Question: How long does the ECB have to request recovery of a sum that was
  overpaid to me?
Example answer: The request for recovery must be made no later than five years from
  the date on which the sum was overpaid or unduly paid. Where the ECB
  is able to establish that the recipient deliberately misled the
  administration in order to obtain the sum, the request for recovery
  shall not be invalidated even after this period has elapsed. (ECB
  Conditions of Employment, page 11)
